    <item>
      <title>Krypto steals the show in Superman teaser</title>
      <author>
          Jennifer Ouellette
        </author>
      <link>https://arstechnica.com/culture/2024/12/krypto-steals-the-show-in-superman-teaser/</link>
      <comments>https://arstechnica.com/culture/2024/12/krypto-steals-the-show-in-superman-teaser/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">662dce2213a184785e0e8cbe4e3452a8851c0738</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 19 Dec 2024 15:23:32 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;         Footage gives us glimpses of Lex Luthor, Green Lantern, Hawkgirl and Superman's plucky little white dog Kryto.       &lt;/p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img width="1152" height="648" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super1-1152x648.jpg" class="intro-image absolute min-w-full min-h-full h-auto object-cover" alt="" loading="eager" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super1-1152x648.jpg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super1-384x216.jpg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super1-768x432.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1152px) 100vw, 1152px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;                       &lt;span class="caption-credit mt-2 text-xs"&gt;           Credit:                       YouTube/DC                    &lt;/span&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;                                                         &lt;figure class="ars-video"&gt;&lt;div class="relative"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/uhUht6vAsMY?start=0&amp;amp;wmode=transparent"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/embed/uhUht6vAsMY?start=0&amp;amp;wmode=transparent&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="caption font-impact dusk:text-gray-300 mb-4 mt-2 inline-flex flex-row items-stretch gap-1 text-base leading-tight text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-300"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-icon bg-[left_top_5px] w-[10px] shrink-0"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-content"&gt;       David Corenswet stars in James Gunn's &lt;em&gt;Superman&lt;/em&gt; reboot.            &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/figure&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Internet has been buzzing the last few days about James Gunn's &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Superman_(2025_film)"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Superman&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; reboot slated for release next year. The studio released a "motion poster" earlier this week set to a moody cover of John Williams' "Superman March," as well as &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KbE8n146umc"&gt;a teaser&lt;/a&gt; for a teaser for the film. That teaser just dropped.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Clearly, given all the buildup, what director James Gunn wants for Christmas is for everyone to get excited over his &lt;em&gt;Superman&lt;/em&gt; movie. And you know what? It kinda worked, especially since Superman's dog Krypto makes an adorably welcome appearance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Gunn describes his take as less of an origin story and more of a journey, with Superman struggling to reconcile his Kryptonian heritage and aristocratic origins with his small-town, adoptive human family. Gunn tapped David Corenswet to play Clark Kent/Superman, at 25 a bit more established than the young cub reporter of &lt;em&gt;Smallville&lt;/em&gt;, for instance. Rachel Brosnahan plays Lois Lane, Skyler Gisondo plays Jimmy Olsen, and Nicholas Holt is arch-nemesis Lex Luther. (Holt's son shaved his head for the role.) Luther's sidekicks are played by Sara Sampaio as Eve Teschmacher and Terence Rosemore as Otis.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The cast also includes Nathan Fillion as Guy Gardner/Green Lantern (sporting a disastrous bowl haircut); Anthony Carrigan as Rex Mason/Metamorpho, who can transmute elements in his body to change forms; Isabela Merced as Hawkgirl; Edi Gathegi as Michael Holt/Mister Terrific, an inventor turned superhero; Maria Gabriela de Faria as Angela Spica/The Engineer, whose abilities stem from embedded nanotechnology; and Pruitt Taylor and Neva Howell as Clark's parents, Jonathan and Martha Kent, respectively. We'll also see Frank Grillo reprise his role as Rick Flag Sr. from the animated series &lt;em&gt;Creature Commandos&lt;/em&gt;; Sean Gunn as Maxwell Lord; and Milly Alcock as Superman's cousin, Kara Zor-El/Supergirl.&lt;/p&gt;                                                                             &lt;div class="ars-lightbox align-fullwidth my-5"&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="1200" height="795" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super2.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="Superman lying on his side in a snow drift, bleeding rom his nose and mouth." loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067731" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super2.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super2-640x424.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super2-1024x678.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super2-768x509.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super2-980x649.jpg 980w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       Our Man of Steel looks a bit battered as he lies in the snow.               &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="1024" height="681" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman9-1024x681.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="Little white dog with a piece of Superman's cape in his mouth, pulling Superman to safety" loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067739" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman9-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman9-640x426.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman9-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman9-980x652.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman9.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       Kypto is a very good boi and saves Superman.               &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="1024" height="681" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super7jpg-1024x681.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="Young man with curly dark hair and glasses sitting at a desk in a newsroom." loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067736" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super7jpg-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super7jpg-640x426.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super7jpg-768x511.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super7jpg-980x652.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super7jpg.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       Superman as his Clark Kent alter-ego is fittingly nebbishy.               &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="640" height="427" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super3-640x427.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="dark haired woman reading a newspaper while standing with a cup of coffee in her hand." loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067732" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super3-640x427.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super3-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super3-980x653.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super3.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       Rachel Brosnahan plays Daily Planet reporter Lois Lane.               &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="640" height="430" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super4-640x430.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="" loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067733" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super4-640x430.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super4-1024x689.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super4-768x516.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super4-980x659.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super4.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       Nicholas Holt partly based his Lex Luthor on Michael Rosenbaum's portrayal in &lt;em&gt;Smallville&lt;/em&gt;/               &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="640" height="432" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super5jpg-640x432.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="Superman crouched inside what looks like a glass cage." loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067734" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super5jpg-640x432.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super5jpg-1024x691.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super5jpg-768x518.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super5jpg-980x662.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super5jpg.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       Superman faces off against Lex Luthor.               &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="640" height="439" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman8-640x439.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="Blond man with bowl haircut shooting green laser light." loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067738" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman8-640x439.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman8-1024x703.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman8-768x527.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman8-980x673.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/superman8.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       That bowl haircut might be iconic for Green Lantern, but it does nothing for Nathan Fillion.               &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="640" height="424" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super6jpg-640x424.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="Superman kneeling over the body of a robot." loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067735" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super6jpg-640x424.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super6jpg-1024x678.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super6jpg-768x509.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super6jpg-980x649.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super6jpg.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       Superman mourns a fallen robot.                &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img decoding="async" width="640" height="427" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super8jpg-640x427.jpg" class="ars-gallery-image" alt="Superman embracing Lois Lane in mid air." loading="lazy" aria-labelledby="caption-2067737" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super8jpg-640x427.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super8jpg-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super8jpg-768x513.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super8jpg-980x654.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/super8jpg.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;       If you could read her mind... Superman + Lois 4 evah               &lt;div class="ars-gallery-caption-credit"&gt;Credit:                        YouTube/DC                   &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The two-minute teaser opens on a desolate snowy landscape as Superman plummets from the sky and hits the ice... hard. He lies there, bloodied and struggling for breath, as we get intercut scenes of him as Clark Kent, of Brosnahan's Lois in the newsroom, of Clark with his dad back on the farm. Then our downed superhero whistles sharply and who should come running but Krypto. "Good dog. Home," Superman rasps. "Take me home."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And the little white dog obliges, taking a piece of cape in his mouth and dragging Superman to safety.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;That's almost the only dialogue in the whole teaser, which just gives us glimpses of the rest of the cast in action. We don't know much about the plot, but it's no surprise that we get some great action shots, including a fire-breathing gigantic monster causing havoc. And there's naturally a budding romance with Clark/Superman and Lois in between all the action. Gunn has a great track record, so we're looking forward to his take on this iconic comic book superhero.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Superman&lt;/em&gt; hits theaters on July 11, 2025.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
